         <p class="- topic/p ">It is important with regular battery
maintenance to ensure that the batteries are in good condition. To
help monitor and maintain the condition of the batteries the Reality
battery management system (G.BMS) can be used. The G.BMS actively
balances and continuously monitors important parameters of each battery
block. For more information please refer to the <xref href="https://Reality.com/Reality/Reality-battery-management-system/"
                  scope="external"
                  class="- topic/xref "
                  format="html">G.BMS Reality Web Page</xref>.</p>
      </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Clean the battery cell covers with damp lint-free cloth.
Check the terminals for any corrosion and if necessary, clean and
slightly grease the poles and links.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <note class="- topic/note ">Only use water to dampen the lint-free cloth. Never use
any solvents or scouring powders.</note>
               <note class="- topic/note ">It is recommended to
use a nonâ€“conductive grease.</note>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Check the tightening torque of the pole screws, see the
documentation from the battery manufacture for torque specifications.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Check the battery with the rectifier switched on. Measure
and record:</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">The battery temperature.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">The string voltage.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Float current.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Inter-cell resistance.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Internal ohmic measurements (impedance), if applicable.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">The voltage of each cell.</p>
                  </li>
               </ul>
               <note class="- topic/note ">The measurements need to be recorded manually or done with
the G.BMS (or other battery management system).</note>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Any other battery maintenance recommended by the manufacturer
of the battery. For more information refer to documentation from the
battery manufacture.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step platform="Modular-DC Modular-AC" class="- topic/li task/step ">
